                       "description":  "<b>Saruman</b> is the master of Orthanc, once the chief of the wise, now the architect of his own dominion.<br><br>His voice bends courts, his mind measures every weakness, and his ambition refuses to wait for permission.<br><br>He builds in silence, gathering strength behind fair words, and he intends to remake the world in the image of his will.<br><br>His design begins with a careful reach into the courts of Rohan, the securing of a pliant voice, and the quiet unearthing of power long buried.<br><br>From Orthanc he turns influence into force and raises the first ranks of his war.",
                       "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\"> <i>Deck identity:</i> The broad Isengard foundation: planning, coercion, furnaces, mixed servants, and practical cruelty in service of controlled expansion.",
                       "variants":  [
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "saruman_the_white",
                                            "displayName":  "The White",
                                            "description":  "<b>Saruman the White</b> stands in the majesty of Orthanc, chief of the Istari, master of lore, ring-craft, and the long devices of the Wise. His voice is a weapon finer than steel, entering the counsels of kings and bending proud hearts with honeyed reason until obedience seems wisdom and surrender seems peace.<br><br>This variant favors influence, manipulation, and command exercised with polished restraint.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\"> <i>Deck identity:</i> Saruman as silver-tongued master of Orthanc, winning by voice, status, and controlled perception rather than raw rush.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "saruman_the_white"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "of_many_colours",
                                            "displayName":  "Of Many Colors",
                                            "description":  "Robed in many colours, <b>the Many-Coloured</b> shatters the white that once signified order and reveals the glittering fracture of pride. In that figure are gathered ring-lore, engines, subtle arts, and the cold brilliance of a mind that would rival the makers of old, yet all are bent now toward dominion, display, and the blasphemous imitation of a power once sent to oppose the Shadow.<br><br>This variant leans into grand sorcery, layered effects, and the dangerous splendor of power unbound by humility.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\"> <i>Deck identity:</i> Saruman's fractured many-coloured persona: self-stylized wizardry, synthesis, vanity, illusion, and magical excess presented as sophistication.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "of_many_colours"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_white_hand",
                                            "displayName":  "The White Hand",
                                            "description":  "<b>The White Hand</b> rises over Isengard like a blasphemous banner, and beneath it the world is remade in smoke, iron, and ruin. Fangorn falls to the axe, the furnaces thunder without ceasing, and from the black pits march Uruk-hai and wolf-riders, forged for the breaking of Helm's Deep and the humiliation of the Mark.<br><br>This variant drives forward with industry, relentless pressure, and the hard discipline of Isengard at war.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\"> <i>Deck identity:</i> Isengard's forged war machine: Uruk discipline, furnace output, siege craft, and fear-driven aggression made systematic.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_white_hand"
                                        }
                                    ],
